{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Tina Cloud (hosted)\n      Tina manages the backend — authentication, git operations, content indexing. You just embed TinaCMS in the Astro site and point it at Tina Cloud. No server to run.\n      \n      \n        How it works\n        \n          Flow per client\n          \n            Client logs in via Tina Cloud (email/password) →\n            Edits content in TinaCMS editor embedded in their site →\n            Tina Cloud commits changes to client's GitHub repo →\n            GitHub Action triggers → Astro build → Cloudflare Pages\n          \n        \n      \n      \n      \n        Pros\n          No server to manage\n          Auth handled out of the box\n          Fastest to get running\n          Scales without effort\n        \n        Cons\n          $29/month (Starter: 2 users, unlimited sites)\n          Vendor dependency for auth + git ops\n          Less control over user management\n        \n      \n      \n      Cost: $29/month flat for all clients (2 users per site). Scales well — same price for 5 or 50 clients.\n      Added complexity vs current setup: Medium — schema definition, template changes, GitHub Action per client. No new infrastructure.","choice":"cloud","id":null,"timestamp":1773998051511}
